				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="524" height="350" src="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/WhatsApp-Image-2018-02-15-at-15.49.03-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="FROM LEFT: President Uhuru Kenyata, former President Jacob Zuma  and former Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn. PHOTO | COURTESY" style="float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;" srcset="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/WhatsApp-Image-2018-02-15-at-15.49.03-1-300x200.jpg 300w, http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/WhatsApp-Image-2018-02-15-at-15.49.03-1.jpg 524w" sizes="(max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px" /><p>The resignation of Ethiopian Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn and South African President Jacob Zuma has evoked a witty response from Kenyans online.</p>
<p>The two resignations hours apart sparked a discussion on Twitter about African leaders&#8217; penchant to hang on to power despite pressure to resign from their citizens.</p>
<p>Some shared a photo of President Uhuru Kenyatta meeting with the two former leaders.</p>
<p>A cheeky tweep suggested Kenyans could donate one of their presidents (Raila or Uhuru) to countries experiencing presidential vacuum.</p>
