<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/news/nairobi-gets-a-new-police-boss-in-major-reshuffle/">Nairobi gets a new police boss in major reshuffle</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke">Nairobi News</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="524" height="350" src="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/koome.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Nairobi County police Commander Japheth Koome has been moved to the police training college in Kiganjo as the commandant. PHOTO | FILE" style="float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;" srcset="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/koome-300x200.jpg 300w, http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/koome.jpg 524w" sizes="(max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px" /><p>Two senior police officers in Nairobi have been moved in a major shakeup of the country&#8217;s top command.</p>
<p>Mr King‚Äôori Mwangi, who was the principal assistant to Deputy Inspector General Edward Mbugua has moved to the police training college in Kiganjo as the commandant.</p>
<p>He is replaced by Nairobi police commander Mr Japheth Koome.</p>
<p>Mr Joseph ole Tito, who is the commandant of the Anti-Stock Theft Unit will now take over the Nairobi command.</p>
<p>And Mr Samuel Kimaru returns to traffic headquarters as commandant from the Central Licensing Bureau.</p>
<p>He is replaced by Mr Nelson Munyi who now becomes the Chief Licensing Officer.</p>
<p>The anti-stock theft unit is now under the command of Mr Joseph Kodi.</p>
<p>Forty officers attached to Kenya Police are affected in the reshuffle.</p>
<p>More changes have been made in the Directorate of Criminal Investigation and the Administration Police, the other arms of the National Police Service and details are expected later.</p>
<p>Other key changes affected, regional commanders, General Service unit, the Presidential Escort, division and county commanders as well as the Traffic department:</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Philip Tuimur from Eastern becomes Director, Community Policing, Children and Gender Affairs.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Larry Kieng from Coast to Director of Personnel.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Moses Ombati from Western to Eastern in equal capacity.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Francis Munyambu moves to Central region as the commander, replacing Mr Gideon Amalla who has<br />
been posted to Interior ministry headquarters.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Mr Peter Ndung‚Äôu becomes Director of Planning from Nairobi traffic command</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ New Nairobi traffic boss is Meshack Musyoki</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Jacinta Muthoni becomes Director of Reforms. She was Traffic Commandant.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Mr Henry Barmao substantially takes charges of Operations directorate where he was acting<br />
director.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Mr Julius Kitili posted to Western as commander. He was director Reforms.</p>
<p>‚Ä¢ Noah Mwivanda takes over as Coast region commander, he was director of Community policing,<br />
Gender and children affairs.</p>
<p>Other officers posted to the ministry are Mr William Saiya and Mr Peter Mwanzia.</p>
