		<title>&#8216;General&#8217; Miguna speaks out as KOT applaud court&#8217;s judgement</title>
		<link>http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/news/general-miguna-speaks-out-as-kot-applaud-courts-judgement/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2018 09:30:23 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Emanuel Onyango]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Also Featured]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Featured]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Canada]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[deportation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[High court]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Luka Kimaru]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Miguna Miguna]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/?p=112329</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p><img width="524" height="350" src="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Miguna Miguna engages his lawyers and nominated Senator Judith Pareno while appearing at Kajiado law courts on February 6, 2018. PHOTO | KANYIRI WAHITO" style="float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;" srcset="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F-300x200.jpg 300w, http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F.jpg 524w" sizes="(max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px" />Fiery Nasa activist vows to continue the "fight against despots" moments after High Court declared his deportation to Canada illegal.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/news/general-miguna-speaks-out-as-kot-applaud-courts-judgement/">&#8216;General&#8217; Miguna speaks out as KOT applaud court&#8217;s judgement</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke">Nairobi News</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="524" height="350" src="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Miguna Miguna engages his lawyers and nominated Senator Judith Pareno while appearing at Kajiado law courts on February 6, 2018. PHOTO | KANYIRI WAHITO" style="float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;" srcset="http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F-300x200.jpg 300w, http://nairobinews.nation.co.ke/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DNCOURTMIGUNA0602F.jpg 524w" sizes="(max-width: 524px) 100vw, 524px" /><p>Fiery Nasa activist Miguna Miguna has vowed to continue the &#8220;fight against despots&#8221; moments after a High Court judge declared his deportation to Canada illegal.</p>
<p>While giving the ruling on Thursday, Justice Luka Kimaru declared that Miguna&#8217;s deportation had no merit in law.</p>
<p>The judge directed the government to deposit Dr Miguna‚Äôs revoked passport at the court within seven days.</p>
<p>In a quick response to the judgement, the self-declared National Resistance Movement general said they will use lawful means in their campaign.</p>
<p>&#8220;We, the #NRMKe, Kenyan patriots and freedom fighters, believe in and are fully committed to the RULE OF LAW. We shall use the CONSTITUTION as the SPEAR and the SHIELD in the fight against the despots,&#8221; he tweeted.</p>
<p>He however gave no indication of making a return to the country.</p>
<p>Miguna filed the suit seeking reinstatement of his Kenyan passport and citizenship on Monday.</p>
<p><strong>TWITTER RESPONSE</strong></p>
<p>Kenyans on Twitter responded with cheer to the High Court judgment.</p>
<p>@ItsOchieng said, ‚ÄúNo retreat no submission. VIVA!‚Äù</p>
<p>@SherryKochiyo tweeted, ‚ÄúWelcome home general.‚Äù</p>
<p>@IvetaLemo commented, ‚ÄúViva!!! So happy you can come back home. Your profound wisdom and knowledge for the Rule of law for some reason gives the despots sleepless nights!! Viva!‚Äù</p>
<p>@Amo_254k wrote, ‚ÄúLooking forward for your grand return to the country viva!General.‚Äù</p>
<p>@markimutai said, ‚Äú7 days is too long&#8230;.The good judge should order the same in court by COB&#8230;!! Welcome back General!‚Äù</p>
<p>@vishasha911 said, ‚ÄúThe welcome ceremony is going to be huuuuuuuge!‚Äù</p>
